The paper deals with the interpretation of the behaviour of recurrent neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of neural networks and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also proposes a novel methodology for interpreting the behaviour of recurrent neural networks, which involves mathematical constructs and algorithms, making it relevant to categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper deals with the applicability and explainability of machine learning methods, which is a topic that falls under the category of cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
